subSubSection.paragraph:
TELEOCONCH. Elevated spire with 5 rounded whorls with impressed suture (
Fig. 25
). Axial sculpture sharp flexuous ribs, approximately 18 per whorl on first 3 whorls; more irregular on body whorl. Microsculpture composed of aligned raised beads on first whorl (
Fig. 27
); coarser and more irregular on subsequent whorls (
Fig. 28
). Narrow, deep, elongated umbilicus at base body whorl partly covered by parietal lip (
Figs 22, 25, 29–30
).
